SIMPLE: footstalk
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Footstalk
<hw>Foot"stalk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The stalk of a leaf or of flower; a petiole,
pedicel, or reduncle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The peduncle or stem
by which various marine animals are attached, as certain brachiopods and
goose barnacles.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The stem which supports which
supports the eye in decapod Crustacea; eyestalk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>The lower part of a millstone
spindle. It rests in a step.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footstall</ent>⟦br⟧
